| Archetype                         |
    14  | 
------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
| --------------------------------- |
    15  | Does it only publish types, schemas, and small invariants?            
| `ARCHETYPE-1-small-contract.md`   |
    16  | Does it wrap an external system behind package-owned ports/adapters?  
| `ARCHETYPE-2-integration.md`      |
    17  | Does it own long-running stateful behavior, lifecycle, or supervised 
execution? | `ARCHETYPE-3-runtime-behavior.md` |
    18  | Is the primary product a fluent DSL or builder API?                   
| `ARCHETYPE-4-dsl-builder.md`      |
    19  | Is it a first-party package under `plugins/*`?                        
| `ARCHETYPE-5-plugin.md`           |
    20  | Does it ship a binary or command-line flow?                           
| `ARCHETYPE-6-cli-tooling.md`      |
    21  
    22  If two archetypes apply, choose the larger one and fold the smaller 
concerns inside it. Do not split
    23  one package across two archetypes.
    24  
